# Work product — keep the reproducible layer, ignore bulk data & rendered blobs.
#
# The team's institutional memory is its *text*: queries (.sql), write-ups
# (FINDINGS.md / SPEC.md / DESIGN.md / MODEL_CARD.md), scripts (.py), specs, and
# inventory READMEs — these stay in git so every number is reproducible and the
# history is auditable (CLAUDE.md principle 3). What's ignored below is the
# large or potentially confidential output: raw extracts, datasets, and rendered
# decks/workbooks/PDFs that can be regenerated from the tracked code.
#
# To preserve a specific output anyway, force-add it: `git add -f path/to/file`.

# Bulk data & extracts (regenerate from the pipeline / query)
*.csv
*.tsv
*.parquet
*.feather
*.avro
*.orc
*.jsonl
*.ndjson
*.sqlite
*.db
*.duckdb

# Rendered deliverables & BI binaries (reproducible from analysis + SOURCES.md)
*.pptx
*.docx
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.pdf
*.twbx
*.twb
*.pbix
*.zip

# Secrets / environment files
.env
.env.*
*.env
secrets.*
*.key
*.pem
credentials.json
service-account*.json

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
*.egg-info/

# Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.gstack/
